09/02/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Police Chief Marijan Benko announced on Thursday (February 8th) a successful police operation that cracked a human trafficking gang in the region, believed responsible for smuggling 300 people into EU countries in the past six months. Benko added that 26 people were arrested, including one Macedonian and one Serbian citizen. Six suspects remain at large. The operation was conducted in co-operation with Bosnian and Slovenian police. During it, police searched 36 apartments in Croatia and a dozen in Bosnia and Herzegovina, all suspected of having been used to house the immigrants along their way. (Vjesnik - 09/02/07; AFP - 08/02/07)
